entry.title: Medlogix Instant Cold Packs 6" x 9", 50/CS
entry.summary:
Vendor: Medlogix
Type: Instant Cold Pack
Price: 46.99

      With an injury, the remedy is often "Put some ice on it" and that's where the Instant Cold Pack comes in handy. Simple and easy to use, the Medlogix Cold Pack is an instant, disposable ice compress that's FDA registered and environmentally-friendly. Simply shake granules in the pack to the bottom of the package, squeeze till inner water bag brakes, shake package to mix contents, wrap package in soft cloth , and apply to injured area. Once activated, cold starts around 30 degrees and ends around 38 degrees. Single-use, non-toxic compress lasts on average 30-35 minutes depending on room temperature. Contains UREA for cold reaction. American made. Whether at home or on the road, be sure your team's first aid station includes the Medlogix Cold Pack.

entry.title: Integra Lifesciences Suture Strip Plus Flexible Wound Closure Strips, ¼" x 4"
entry.summary:
Vendor: Integra LifeSciences
Type: Suture Strip
Price: 70.62

The Integra LifeSciences Suture Strip® Plus Flexible Wound Closure Strips offer superior closure for surface tissue wounds or traumatic wounds such as skin tears.

It is made of macroporous non-woven polyamide with a pressure-sensitive adhesive that imitates the elasticity of human skin. Suture Strip® Plus effortlessly elongates and yields according to skin movement, which prevents force from concentrating at the proximal ends. This reduces the chances of blisters or skin shear due to traction. The skin-friendly adhesive offers optimum adherence. Suture Strip® Plus is sterile, latex-free and does not irritate sensitive skin. Ideal for wounds and even for plastic surgery, to ensure that aesthetic results are maintained.

Product Highlights

  • Macroporous non-woven polyamide
  • Pressure-sensitive adhesive
  • Superior elasticity and adherence
  • Skin-friendly and reduces chances of irritation

10/BX
